This paper deals with learning theory and specifically with the problem of identifying if two distributions are identical when we have access only to examples sampled from the distributions. This is a fundamental problem in machine learning and is relevant to several subfields such as generative adversarial networks (GANs). The paper introduces a new type of discriminator called k-ary based discriminators, which are based on hyper-graphs. The paper also studies the expressiveness and sample complexity of these discriminators. Given the focus on learning theory and machine learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
